Security Agencies In Nairobi Led By The Head Of Flying Squad Musa Yego And Nairobi Regional Commander Philip Ndolo Have Now Began Investigations Into The Killings Of Two Police Officers At Saika Area Of Kayole Estate In Nairobi. According To Eyewitnesses Who Sought Anonymity, The Two Officers Who Were On Patrol Were Shot Dead By Two Men On A Motorbike At The Wee Hours On Friday Before Escaping. The Killers Also Took Away Their Guns. Kayole OCPD Wilson Kosgey Who Confirmed The Incident But Did Not Speak On Camera Said Investigations Into The Killings Have Began And That The Perpetrators Will Soon Be Brought To Book.